events.title: International Human Rights Day
events.description:
üåç International Human Rights Day reminds us that equality isn‚Äôt optional, it‚Äôs a human right.

Observed every year on December 10, this day marks the anniversary of the Universal Declaration of Human Rights (UDHR), adopted by the United Nations in 1948. It was the first global statement to affirm that every person is born free and equal in dignity and rights, regardless of who they are or whom they love.

üè≥Ô∏è‚Äçüåà Today, as LGBTQIA+ communities continue to face discrimination, violence, legislative rollbacks, and efforts to restrict visibility and bodily autonomy, this reminder is more urgent than ever. Human rights protections must include gender identity, sexual orientation, access to healthcare, safety, and the freedom to live authentically.

At IMPAQT GSO, we believe that advancing LGBTQIA+ rights is inseparable from advancing human rights. Our community is stronger together, and together we continue the fight for equity, dignity, and justice.

‚ú® Equality is a human right, for ALL of us.

#InternationalHumanRightsDay #HumanRights #LGBTQRightsAreHumanRights #IMPAQTGSO #Respect #Inclusivity #Pride #GSOPride

events.title: LEAF LITTER Exhibition
events.description:
We‚Äôre thrilled to spotlight a truly captivating series in our current exhibition, LEAF LITTER‚Äî‚ÄòAbalone Variation 1‚Äì6‚Äô by the talented artist KT Wilson. These original works are a celebration of the subtle, often overlooked wonders of nature, and we invite you to experience them in person at Irving Park Art & Frame.
Each piece in this series features a sustainably sourced abalone shell (pƒÅua) from the pristine waters of New Zealand. Revered for their iridescent beauty and cultural significance, New Zealand abalone shells are harvested under one of the world‚Äôs most robust sustainability systems, ensuring that their natural populations are protected for generations to come. These shells, considered ‚Äòtaonga‚Äô (treasures) in MƒÅori culture, are not only a feast for the eyes but also a testament to the harmony of art and ecological responsibility‚Å†.
KT Wilson‚Äôs approach transforms each shell into a meditative focal point by mounting them in custom shadowbox frames. Rather than traditional fastenings, Wilson uses carefully woven textiles and thread to cradle each shell in place. This technique both secures the shell and highlights its natural form, color, and texture, drawing attention to the unique qualities of each specimen. The interplay between the organic shell and the geometric textile work invites viewers to contemplate the contrast and connection between the natural world and human creativity.
The ‚ÄòAbalone Variation‚Äô series is a perfect fit for LEAF LITTER, our exhibition dedicated to the nuanced, often unnoticed aspects of nature. This show brings together artists whose work delves into the delicate, the intricate, and the ephemeral‚Äîreminding us that beauty is often found in quiet details. KT Wilson‚Äôs pieces exemplify this ethos, offering viewers a chance to slow down and appreciate the subtle complexity of natural materials and thoughtful craft.
.
Visit us at Irving Park Art & Frame to see KT Wilson‚Äôs work and explore the full LEAF LITTER exhibition. Support local art, sustainable materials, and the ongoing conversation between human hands and the natural world.
.
.
.
#ArtExhibition #ContemporaryArt #NatureInspired #KTWilson #AbaloneArt #SustainableArt #PauaShel

events.title: Hustle Souls Live Performance
events.description:
Tonight, Saturday the 3rd!
Doors at 7:30pm
Show at 8:30pm

Hustle Souls, based in Asheville, NC, masterfully blend Retro-Soul, New Orleans Brass, and Singer-Songwriter Americana into a unique and captivating sound. Lauded by American Blues Scene as a ‚Äúgeneration-jumping mashup of new school second line funk with old school vintage soul,

‚Äú and described by Bluestown Music as ‚Äúintimate soul‚Ä¶with a Curtis Mayfield like warmth,‚Äù the band has earned a spot as one of Music Connection Magazine‚Äôs ‚ÄúHot 100 Live Unsigned Artists & Bands‚Äù and No Treble shared the band saying ‚ÄúI hadn‚Äôt heard them before, but I‚Äôm glad I have now‚Ä¶ Must See‚ÄùOverflowing with energy and spontaneity, Hustle Souls features roaring B3 organ and jubilant trumpet and trombone, balanced with three-part vocal harmonies and a passion for songwriting. Their music has been praised by Aldora Britian Records as ‚Äúworthy of being included in that brilliant soul music canon, a heritage that features some of the greatest performers and writers that have ever graced this earth.

Africa Unplugged is a dynamic group, led by djembe master, guitarist and songwriter, Atiba Rorie. The band uses traditional percussion instruments from West Africa in combination with guitars and bass to play traditional rhythms while drawing from influences across the world. Their creativity results in a funky, soulful blues and dance music that keeps you moving as they tell stories from the old world and the new!

events.title: Demonstration Against Injustice
events.description:
Shout out to all the comrades and organizations that have been organizing this demonstration for months, thank you to all the comrades who raised their voices today against injustice and to call for unity in the community, in the class, and to call for solidarity. Today we just wanted to have a demonstration to tell the new administration that here in the Triad we are organized and that there is a resistance that will defend our rights and that if they touch one of us, we will all come out. We invite you, members of the community, whether you are part of an organization or not, who wants to collaborate, who is frustrated with what is happening and doesn‚Äôt know how to help, who want to understand and get more information, we invite you to ORGANIZE yourself by getting in touch with us or any organization that best suits you. We also want to make a call to the organizations that want to do things together to join us, we must open the channels of communication and support each other. We have many different tasks but the adversary is the same and in the end the fight is also for the same thing. So let‚Äôs organize, let‚Äôs fight together!  Please stay tuned for the next events, actions etc.
 Group of revolutionary socialists in Greensboro, NC and members of Tempest Collective @tempest_mag

events.title: Mobilization Against the New Donald Trump Administration
events.description:
On January 25th we will mobilize against the new Donald Trump administration to send a clear message‚Ä¶ that we are ready to continue fighting and resisting to defend the rights of the majority and to say that this administration does not represent us either! We will be united not only for this demonstration but ready to act together at any time. We will support and defend the most vulnerable members of our community from any impending redoubled attacks. We invite you (triad community) to join this coalition on the 25th and to continue organizing and opening channels of communication and staying united, knowing that we must face our common enemy together.  We keep us safe!
 Group of revolutionary socialists in Greensboro, NC and members of Tempest Collective @tempest_mag
